	SELECT [FIELD] fname [[SOUNDING] id]

The SELECT command chooses a field to be edited.  The field is specified by
'fname' and the sounding may be specified by 'id'.  If no sounding is
given, the current default sounding will be used.  If a field which is in
the current plot is SELECTed, a cursor will appear on the screen at the
first point of the selected field.

